<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-08-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-08-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="382" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d382">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Eddy</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                        Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-08-23"><hi rend="italic">August 23,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 634.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I beg leave to confirm herewith my
                            cablegram of to-day sent en clair, as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>All strikes concluded, Reval; factories have resumed work.</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Spencer Eddy</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>